Assignment II – CI/CD Pipeline using Jenkins (DSO101)
Project Overview

This assignment aimed to implement a Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) pipeline using Jenkins for a Node.js Todo application developed in Assignment I.
The pipeline was expected to automate the following processes:
Code checkout from GitHub
Dependency installation (npm)
Build process
Unit testing using Jest/Mocha
Deployment using Docker

The goal was to demonstrate full CI/CD automation using Jenkins.

Tools & Technologies
Jenkins (CI/CD automation tool)
GitHub (source code repository)
Node.js & npm (application runtime)
Jest (unit testing framework)
Docker (planned for deployment)

Intended CI/CD Pipeline Design
A Jenkins pipeline (Jenkinsfile) was prepared with the following stages:

Checkout source code from GitHub
Install dependencies using npm install
Build the application
Run unit tests using Jest
Deploy application using Docker

This pipeline was designed according to standard CI/CD practices.

Implementation Status

The Jenkins CI/CD pipeline was not fully implemented or executed successfully.

The following issues occurred:
Jenkins was not successfully connected to the GitHub repository
Pipeline was not triggered or executed inside Jenkins
Build, test, and deployment stages were not completed
Docker deployment stage was not implemented successfully
End-to-end CI/CD automation was not achieved

As a result, the pipeline remained in a theoretical and partially configured state rather than a fully working system.

Challenges Faced
During the implementation, several technical challenges were encountered:

Difficulty in configuring Jenkins plugins and Node.js environment
Issues connecting GitHub repository with Jenkins pipeline
Lack of successful pipeline execution due to setup errors
Docker integration not completed due to environment configuration problems
Limited successful testing of CI/CD workflow

Learning Outcome
Even though the pipeline was not fully completed, this assignment helped in understanding:

How Jenkins pipelines are structured
The role of CI/CD in modern software development
Integration between GitHub, Jenkins, and Docker
Importance of environment configuration in DevOps workflows

This experience provided foundational knowledge of CI/CD systems and highlighted real-world challenges in pipeline setup.

📚 Conclusion

The CI/CD pipeline for the Todo application was designed and partially implemented but not fully executed due to configuration and integration issues in Jenkins.

However, the assignment still demonstrates understanding of CI/CD concepts, pipeline architecture, and DevOps workflow design.